# __ARDUINO : Register Tweaks

### Creating a traffic light signal using 3 LED's and 1 push button to turn on and off the LEDs. Also implement Hardware Debounce circuitry for the push button.
### Note: you should change values in registers DDRx PINx PORTx for GPIO, and should not use pinMode(), digitalRead()/Write() functions in your code You can use tinkercad or wokwi.com as simulation platform

## **CODE**
```c++
void setup() {
  DDRB = B000111;  
  PORTD = B00000100;
}
int a=1;
void loop() {
  if(PIND & B00000100){
    PORTB &= B000000;
  }
  if(!(PIND & B00000100)){
    if (a==1){
      PORTB |= B000100;
      delay(1000);
      a++;
    }
    else if (a==2){
      PORTB |= B000010;
      delay(1000);
      a++;
    }
    else if (a==3){
      PORTB |= B000001;
      delay(1000);
      a=a-2;
    }
  PORTB &= B000000; 
  }
}    
```
***
 > The above is a simple 3 led system >
 controled by 1 push button using register >
 manipulation in arduino/ direvtly implementing binary values to arduino registres.
